# FlashQuery Macro Testing Framework — gitignore policy
#
# COMMITTED: test cases (cases/), the coverage matrix (coverage/), the golden
# model source (macro-golden-model/src/), the framework harness (src/), the
# runnable pipeline scripts (scripts/), gap logs, the eval log, and the README.
#
# GITIGNORED: ephemeral run output and quarantined scratch.
#
# See the framework requirements doc §9.4 / §9.6 for the rationale behind the
# committed surfaces.

# ─── Negate parent gitignore rule for `coverage/` ──────────────────────────
# The repo-root .gitignore ignores `coverage/` (intended for nyc/istanbul
# output). That unanchored rule would also match our coverage-matrix directory.
# Per §9.4 the coverage matrix MUST be committed (manifest.ts, coverage.json,
# MTF_COVERAGE.md, MTF_INTERACTIONS.md), so we re-include it here.
!coverage/
!coverage/**

# ─── Fresh-cadence generated tests ─────────────────────────────────────────
# Per §5.5 fresh mode: tests generated on each CI run, never committed.
cases-fresh/

# ─── Failure-triage records — runtime output ───────────────────────────────
# The runner writes a record into failures/ on a genuine FAIL. These are
# ephemeral run output, not committed artifacts. Keep the directory itself
# (via the .gitkeep) but ignore everything written into it.
failures/*
!failures/.gitkeep

# ─── Quarantined scratch ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# One-off probes, dead scaffolding, and other throwaway files live in
# _scratch/. Nothing here is load-bearing — delete the directory at will.
# (Load-bearing tools live in scripts/ and are committed. Do NOT gitignore
# files by a leading-underscore name convention — that rule previously hid
# the capture runner and the P/G diff from version control.)
_scratch/

# ─── macOS / editor cruft ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
.idea/
.vscode/

# ─── Logs / temp ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.log
tmp/
.cache/
